    • Constructor Detail

      • ClassDefinition

        public ClassDefinition​(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
                throws ImplerException
        Constructs class definition based on type token clazz.
        Every SecurityException will be ignored and skipped for further generating of class body. Resulting definition will be a correct java code of non-abstract class with name Class.getSimpleName() + "Impl".
        Parameters:
        clazz - type token which definition will be generated
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if clazz is not an open class or an inteface.

        Parameters:

        Throws:
        ImplerException - if class is not satisfies required constraints.

      • collectMethodInfo

        private java.lang.String collectMethodInfo​(int modifiers,
                                           java.lang.String methodName,
                                           java.lang.Class<?>[] arguments,
                                           java.lang.Class<?>[] exceptions,
                                           java.lang.String body)
        Generates method definition based on it's signature.
        Method arguments will receive names according to generateArgumentName(int)
        Parameters:
        modifiers - Modifier mask that will be used for generating method modifiers.
        methodName - name of the method, including it's return type.
        arguments - types that this method accepts.
        exceptions - exception types that this method throws.
        body - body of this method.
        Returns:
        compilable method source code with name of methodName, arguments of arguments, exceptions of exceptions, body of body and modifiers of modifiers.

      • generateConstructor

        private java.lang.String generateConstructor​(java.lang.reflect.Constructor<?> ctor)
        Generates constructor source code based on ctor type information. Constructor body will be just an indirection to corresponding superclass constuctor.
        Parameters:
        ctor - Constructor which definition will be generated.
        Returns:
        source code for constructor with signature of ctor.

      • generateMethod

        private java.lang.String generateMethod​(java.lang.reflect.Method method)
        Generates method source code based on method type information. Method body will be just return some default value for Method.getReturnType().
        Parameters:
        method - method which definition will be generated
        Returns:
        source code for method with signature of ctor

      • isMethodAcceptable

        private boolean isMethodAcceptable​(java.lang.reflect.Method m)
        Determines if method is required to implement. Filters final, native, volatile methods.
        Parameters:
        m - method that will be analyzed.
        Returns:
        true, if method is allowed to be overridden or false otherwise.

      • getImplementableMethods

        private java.util.Set<java.lang.reflect.Method> getImplementableMethods()
        Generates Set of implementable methods.
        This method gets Class.getMethods() and Class.getDeclaredMethods() and then filters them using isMethodAcceptable(Method)
        Returns:
        Set of methods that will be overridden in generated class definition.

        Parameters:
